KATSINA – Malam Dikko Umar Radda, the governor of Katsina State, has appointed Architect Ahmed Musa Dangiwa, his campaign DG, as the new Secretary to the State Government (SSG). The appointment which is coming barely a few hours after assuming office is contained in a statement personally signed by the governor and made available to newsmen in Katsina on Tuesday. Other appointees include Alhaji Jabiru Tsauri as the Chief of Staff, Muhtar Aliyu Saulawa as the Deputy Chief of Staff and Alhaji Abdullahi Aliyu Turaji as the Principal Private Secretary to the Governor. The governor also approved the appointments of Mallam Maiwada Danmallam, Director General Media; Ibrahim Kaula Mohammed, Chief Press Secretary; Malam Miqdad Isah as Senior Special Assistant (Digital Media) and Abubakar Badaru Jikamshi as the Senior Special Assistant (Print and Electronic Media). Alhaji Bishir Maikano is the Senior Special Assistant (Protocol) Deputy Governor’s Office, Alhaji Hassan Ibrahim Danhaire as Senior Special Assistant (Special Duties) Deputy Governor’s Office and Ahmed Rabiu as Official Photographer to the Governor. The governor congratulated the new appointees and urged them to join hands with him in turning around the fortunes of the state.